**Approach 1** (Two Pointer Technique) is optimal with a linear time complexity of O(n+m)O(n+m)O(n+m), making it ideal when the arrays are already sorted.
**Approach 2** (Using a Set) offers a simpler solution by leveraging built-in data structures to handle uniqueness automatically, though it may incur additional log factors due to ordering.
